name: Casa do Faroleiro 4
description: According to some historians, the Spanish navigator Vicente Yañez Pinzón arrived in the Cabo de Santo Agostinho region (PE, Brazil) and discovered Brazil three months before the Portuguese Pedro Álvares Cabral arrived in Bahia. In Cabo, there is the old village of Nazaré, with the ruins of Casa do Faroleiro. Just as historical views are multiple, photography also assumes multiple exposure. An orientation point for navigation multiplies in different perspectives. 4160 x 6240 mauriciomessa.com.br
